Eskom has stated that it will implement stage 3 load-shedding today, 12 February. The load-shedding will run from 08:00 and is likely to continue until 23:00. This latest batch of load-shedding follows Eskom implementing stage 4 load-shedding on Monday – after seven generating units went offline. The power utility asked customers to please use electricity sparingly today. Users were also advised to consult their load-shedding schedules for today’s power cuts. The load-shedding announcement is detailed in the tweet below. 